# London Community Fest — Cursor Rules

## Project
Community festival website that will evolve into a SaaS platform (Community Event OS).
Built by a solo founder using AI-assisted development. Code quality matters — no throwaway work.

## Stack
- Next.js 16 (App Router)
- React 19
- TypeScript (strict)
- Tailwind CSS 4 (uses @theme inline in globals.css, NOT tailwind.config.ts)
- No shadcn/ui — UI primitives are hand-built in components/ui/

## Architecture Rules
- All event data lives in lib/config/ — never hardcode dates, venue, pricing in components
- All reusable types live in types/index.ts — split into separate files only when index exceeds 40 lines
- All static content arrays (FAQ items, activities, sponsor tiers) live in data/ folder
- Components import data, they don't define it
- Use "as const" on all config exports
- Use the cn() utility from lib/utils.ts for conditional class merging

## Folder Structure (enforced)
- app/ — routes and layouts only
- components/landing/ — landing page section components
- components/ui/ — reusable UI primitives (button, container, section-heading)
- data/ — static content arrays
- lib/config/ — site, event, and navigation configuration
- lib/ — utilities and helpers
- types/ — TypeScript interfaces
- hooks/ — custom React hooks

## Component Rules
- One component per file
- Named exports only (no default exports except page.tsx and layout.tsx)
- Props must be typed with interface, not inline
- Keep components under 150 lines — split if larger
- No "use client" unless the component genuinely needs browser APIs or state

## Visual Design Direction (LOCKED)
Source of truth: `lib/config/design.ts` + `app/globals.css` @theme tokens.
Reference implementation: `components/landing/` (poster-style demo) and `components/ui/paper-card.tsx`, `polaroid.tsx`.

**Brand references**
- Official logo: crimson `#7A0D22` (`crimson-400`) + slate `#475059` (`slate-500`) — `public/images/logo.png`
- Marketing mood: WhatsApp festival poster — collage/scrapbook, handcrafted, not corporate SaaS

**Mood & layout**
- Torn parchment cards (`PaperCard`, `paper-torn`), polaroid photos with tape (`Polaroid`, `tape-strip`)
- Subtle grain on dark sections (`poster-grain`)
- Layered collage: tilted polaroids, overlapping “Fest” accent, icon strip on parchment

**Colour roles (do not swap arbitrarily)**
| Role | Token | Use |
|------|-------|-----|
| Dark hero/collage bg | `forest-900`, `forest-800` | Main dark sections + grain |
| Brand / CTA / Fest accent | `crimson-400`–`crimson-500` | Logo colour, buttons, footer bar |
| Logo secondary / muted text | `slate-500` | “Community” labels, muted on light |
| Price / highlight | `gold-400` | £3, clocks, emphasis on dark |
| Parchment UI | `paper-50`–`paper-200` | Cards, date blocks, skyline strip |
| Text on dark | `cream`, `cream-muted` | Headlines, taglines on forest |
| Text on light | `ink`, `ink-muted` | Body on paper sections |

**Typography**
- `font-sans` (Be Vietnam Pro): caps labels, dates, pricing, UI
- `font-serif` (Instrument Serif): tagline, “Fest” accent, year on date card
- Hero pattern: uppercase sans “LONDON COMMUNITY” + large italic serif crimson “Fest”

**Section rhythm (alternate dark → paper → dark → crimson footer)**
1. Hero — `bg-forest-900 poster-grain`
2. Collage / content — `bg-forest-800` or `bg-paper-100`
3. Pricing strip — `bg-forest-900`, gold price
4. Footer — `bg-paper-100` skyline, then `bg-crimson-500` contact bar

## Styling Rules
- Tailwind CSS 4 utility classes only — no inline styles, no CSS modules
- Custom colours ONLY from globals.css @theme inline — no new hex in components
- Read `lib/config/design.ts` before adding new sections or UI patterns
- Font classes: font-serif (Instrument Serif), font-sans (Be Vietnam Pro)
- Dark sections: forest/crimson backgrounds + cream/gold text
- Light sections: paper backgrounds + ink text

## Code Quality
- No any types
- No console.log in committed code
- No unused imports
- No giant files — if a component needs 200+ lines, it should be split
- Prefer early returns over nested conditionals
- Comments only when explaining WHY, not WHAT

## What NOT to Do
- Do not install shadcn/ui or Radix
- Do not create tailwind.config.ts — Tailwind 4 uses CSS-based config
- Do not add state management libraries (no Zustand, Redux)
- Do not add dark mode toggle — light/dark is controlled per-section
- Do not create pages beyond app/page.tsx until explicitly asked
- Do not use Geist fonts — project uses Instrument Serif and Be Vietnam Pro
- Do not drift from the poster direction: no flat white SaaS heroes, no purple/blue gradients, no zinc/gray Tailwind defaults
- Do not invent new colour tokens without updating globals.css @theme and lib/config/design.ts together
